  "prompt": "What is months at level in Accenture?",
  "response": "In Accenture, the term \"months at level\" typically refers to the amount of time an employee has spent at their current job level or position within the company. This can be a factor in promotions and career progression, as employees often need to meet certain time requirements at their level before being considered for advancement to a higher position. \n\nThe specific requirements for months at level can vary depending on the individual's career path, role, and performance. For instance, different functions within Accenture (like consulting, technology, or operations) may have different expectations regarding the timeline for promotions. \n\nIf you are looking for details specific to your career path at Accenture or how this impacts your development, it might be best to consult directly with your manager or a human resources representative within the company.",
